I would like to say please experience somewhere for yourself. Someone else's review will not be your exact experience.  I've eaten here close to 10x and last night probably being my 10th after a 2yr hiatus from them. The owner is always nice. The staff are always friendly. I am African American myself and have never experienced lesser treatment nor disrespect from any staff there based on my complexion. I was pleasantly surprised that after not eating here for 2yrs and cutting all my hair off the owner STILL remembered me and gave me the most gracious welcome, with the biggest smile upon walking thru the door. I approached the counter in shock asking if he really did remember me and his reply was, "You're the nurse that use to have long hair." I was flattered and honored. That's customer service!!  I usually get the chicken kabob platter so that's what I ordered. I wanted to try the lamb kabob so I asked if he could add it to it. He politely suggested I order the chicken/lamb kabob platter which would save me more money. And I did. A+!! While waiting for my food he came from behind the counter to converse and he even remembered my boyfriend too who is now my fiance! Just awesome. This establishment is one with customer service you desire in your neighborhood.  The food is always good/fresh, Nan made fresh always right in front of you. Everything prepared in front of you. Because I ordered 2 kabobs instead of 1, the owner made sure the staff member put extra sauces (4) in my bag.  What you give is what you get. And because I am always gracious, have good energy, a genuine smile, and non-judgemental...guess what?? Its reciprocated. Be blessed.

If you're looking for a little authentic hole in the wall, this is not the place.  We should have known to turn back the second we saw the outside, but we had walked for a while to find it, and sadly gave in.  The inside has stock imagery of items not actually on their menu, and also some signs of a different restaurant name? The service was terrible.  We were the only customers there, which is never a good sign either... To begin with, the woman who took our order was rude and didn't even get off of the phone from her personal call talking to a friend in spanish.  Then she orders a young kid to make the food.  She continues her conversation and he starts the food. No rushing happening here...There were many places for food to be out in the open, like chaffing dishes, yet no food in sight.  The one sad dry looking kabob in the corner had me worried.  Around 15 minutes later, she takes a breath from her conversation to tell us we can come pick up the food from the counter.  Don't bother bringing it to us...seeing as we are the only people there... The food could have been good.  I gave it a chance...two different kinds of bland rice, dry meat and ranch dressing.  Yes that's right, not kebob sauce or yogurt, ranch dressing folks.  The music was equally depressing, some lame mix of 80's and top 40, all combining to make this by far the worst meal we had in DC.  Steer clear kabob lovers, the service, food and atmosphere at this place are a total waste of your time.

A group of friends and I visited this place over the weekend. The food was probably good - if they would've let us eat it. We have NEVER experienced such HORRIFIC attitude from anyone. We ordered and received our food and sat down to eat (the food staff was fine). There were plenty of other people eating in peace as well in the establishment. 2 of our friends stepped outside to have a conversation, which took about 3 minutes, and meanwhile we were still inside eating. When they tried to come back in, a man who was apparently the "security" there told them they can't come in, the place is now closed. Again, there were many others aside from our group eating in peace. Our friend said we've already got our food and that he just wanted to join us to finish eating. After calmly discussing this and the man saying 'no entry', the man shoved our friend back. At this point he got agitated and said 'don't shove me, don't touch me, I'm not doing anything wrong, I just want to eat with my friends". The security guy was came to our table, grabbed all our food trays (WHILE  we were eating), and upended everything onto the table and floor. The other customers were shocked as to what was happening as well. Meanwhile, other new customers were coming into the place to order without ANY issues?! We were not belligerent, or drunk, or rude, until the security decided he wanted us out, while other people were allowed to eat in peace. HE THREW OUR FOOD, THAT WE PAID FOR AND WERE EATING, ONTO THE FLOOR?? WHO THE HELL DOES THAT? If I could give negative ratings this place would get it. It was the MOST unreasonable, rude, and hateful thing we have experienced in a very, very long time. This man needs to be fired. We also took video of what happened that we will be sharing with their management and BBB. Absolutely disrespectful and ridiculous.
